.SH "NAME"
TV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper \- TrecVid08 Big XML Files Validator Helper
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
\&\fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR [\-\-help\ |\ \-\-man\ |\ \-\-version]
  [\fB\-\-xmllint\fR\ \fIlocation\fR]\ [\fB\-\-TrecVid08xsd\fR\ \fIlocation\fR]
  [\fB\-\-ViperValidator\fR\ \fIlocation\fR]\ [\fB\-\-MergeHelper\fR\ \fIlocation\fR]
  [\fB\-\-gtf\fR]\ [\fB\-\-splitevery\fR\ \fIvalue\fR]\ [\fB\-\-chunks\fR\ \fIbytes\fR]
  [\fB\-\-quiet\fR]\ [\fB\-\-Copy_xml_too\fR]
  \fB\-\-fps\fR \fIfps\fR \fB\-\-writedir\fR \fIdirectory\fR
  \fIviper_source_file.xml\fR [\fIviper_source_file.xml\fR [\fI...\fR]]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR performs a syntactic and semantic validation of the ViPER \s-1XML\s0 file(s) provided on the command line, then write a MemDump version of this file into the \fBwritedir\fR directory. It can \fIvalidate\fR reference files (see \fB\-\-gtf\fR) as well as system files. It does so by splitting large files into plenty of small files, validating those files and merging the resulting files. It does not have all the options of TV08ViperValidator as it is a helper tool designed to obtain a MemDump version of large \s-1XML\s0 files. Those MemDump files can then be used in other tools reducing considerably the load time (does not have to re-validate the \s-1XML\s0 file).
.SH "PREREQUISITES"
.IX Header "PREREQUISITES"
\&\fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR relies on some external software and files.
.IP "\fB\s-1SOFTWARE\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "SOFTWARE"
\&\fIxmllint\fR (part of \fIlibxml2\fR, see http://www.xmlsoft.org/) is required (at least version 2.6.30) to perform the syntactic validation of the source file.
If \fIxmllint\fR is not available in your \s-1PATH\s0, you can specify its location either on the command line (see \fB\-\-xmllint\fR) or by setting the F4DE_XMLLINT environment variable.
.Sp
\&\fBTV08ViperValidator\fR and \fBTV08MergerHelper\fR, part of F4DE's TrecVid08 section are also needed as they are the core programs used.
.IP "\fB\s-1FILES\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "FILES"
The syntactic validation requires some \s-1XML\s0 schema files (full list can be obtained using the \fB\-\-help\fR option).
It is possible to specify their location using the \fB\-\-xsdpath\fR option.
You should not have to specify their location, if you have performed an install and have set the global environment variables.
.IP "\fB\s-1GLOBAL\s0 \s-1ENVIRONMENT\s0 \s-1VARIABLES\s0\fR" 4
.IX Item "GLOBAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES"
Once you have installed the software, extending your \fB\s-1PATH\s0\fR to include F4DE's \fBbin\fR directory should be sufficient for the tools to find their components.
.SH "GENERAL NOTES"
.IX Header "GENERAL NOTES"
\&\fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR expect that the files can be validated using 'xmllint' against the TrecVid08 \s-1XSD\s0 file(s) (see \fB\-\-help\fR for files list).
.PP
\&\fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR will ignore the \fIconfig\fR section of the \s-1XML\s0 file, as well as discard any xml comment(s).
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
.IP "\fB\-\-Copy_xml_too\fR" 4
.IX Item "--Copy_xml_too"
Copy source \s-1XML\s0 file to \fBwritedir\fR directory in addition to generating the \fIMemDump\fR file.
.IP "\fB\-\-chunks\fR \fIvalue\fR" 4
.IX Item "--chunks value"
Read \fIvalue\fR bytes of data at a time from the source file when generating the sub files used for validation.
This influence the speed of processing of the validation process.
Default value can be obtained using \fB\-\-help\fR. It is recommended to not go under this value.
.IP "\fB\-\-fps\fR \fIfps\fR" 4
.IX Item "--fps fps"
Specify the default sample rate (in frames per second) of the ViPER files.
.IP "\fB\-\-gtf\fR" 4
.IX Item "--gtf"
Specify that the file to validate is a Reference file (also known as a Ground Truth File)
.IP "\fB\-\-help\fR" 4
.IX Item "--help"
Display the usage page for this program. Also display some default values and information.
.IP "\fB\-\-MergeHelper\fR \fIlocation\fR" 4
.IX Item "--MergeHelper location"
Specify the location of the TV08MergeHelper program (used by this helper).
Default location used can be obained using \fB\-\-help\fR.
.IP "\fB\-\-man\fR" 4
.IX Item "--man"
Display this man page.
.IP "\fB\-\-quiet\fR" 4
.IX Item "--quiet"
Do not print processing information (default is to be verbose).
.IP "\fB\-\-splitevery\fR \fIvalue\fR" 4
.IX Item "--splitevery value"
Split the source file every \fIvalue\fR event observation seen.
This influence the total number of files created in the validation process.
Default value can be obtained using \fB\-\-help\fR
.IP "\fB\-\-TrecVid08xsd\fR \fIlocation\fR" 4
.IX Item "--TrecVid08xsd location"
Specify the default location of the required \s-1XSD\s0 files (use \fB\-\-help\fR to get the list of required files).
.IP "\fB\-\-ViperValidator\fR \fIlocation\fR" 4
.IX Item "--ViperValidator location"
Specify the location of the TV08ViperValidator program (used by this helper).
Default location used can be obained using \fB\-\-help\fR.
.IP "\fB\-\-version\fR" 4
.IX Item "--version"
Display \fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR version information.
.IP "\fB\-\-writedir\fR [\fIdirectory\fR]" 4
.IX Item "--writedir [directory]"
Once validation has been completed for a given file, \fBTV08_BigXML_ValidatorHelper\fR will write the MemDump representation of this file to this directory.
.IP "\fB\-\-xmllint\fR \fIlocation\fR" 4
.IX Item "--xmllint location"
Specify the full path location of the \fBxmllint\fR command line tool if not available in your \s-1PATH\s0.
Can also be set using the \fBF4DE_XMLLINT\fR environment variable.
